Analysis of Target Image  
• Total Blocks & Layers  
  – There are 5 total blocks in the structure.  
  – They are arranged in three layers:  
    1) Bottom layer: 3 red arch‐shaped blocks side‐by‐side.  
    2) Middle layer: 1 green rectangular block resting on top of (and spanning) the center of the bottom blocks.  
    3) Top layer: 1 red arch‐shaped block sitting on the green block.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The three red arches on the bottom are placed in a row, all oriented so the arches face front‐to‐back in the same way.  
  – The single green rectangular block lies horizontally above the center bottom arch (covering part of the left and right arches as well).  
  – One more red arch block is centered directly on top of the green block, again with its arch facing front‐to‐back.  

Selection of Required Blocks  
• From the dictionary, the four red arches match block index “1” (the same shape/orientation each time).  
• The horizontal green rectangle matches block index “9.”  

Hence, the needed block indices are:  
• Red arch block: 1 (used four times)  
• Green rectangular block: 9 (used once)  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  // bottom‐left red arch  
  Step2: Move block with index 1  // bottom‐center red arch  
  Step3: Move block with index 1  // bottom‐right red arch  
  Step4: Move block with index 9  // horizontal green block on top of center arch  
  Step5: Move block with index 1  // final red arch on top  
}
